-- Russia Equity Movers: United Co. Rusal, KamAZ Shares Are Active
-- B y   J a c k   J o r d a n
-- 2012-03-19T14:37:32Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-19/russia-equity-movers-united-co-rusal-kamaz-shares-are-active.html
The 30-stock Micex index lost 1.9
percent to 1,587.84 as of 5:52 p.m. in Moscow, heading for the
biggest daily drop since March 6. The dollar-denominated RTS
index lost 1.5 percent to 1,722.04.  The following are among the most active equities in the
Russian market today. Stock symbols are in parentheses.  OAO KamAZ (KAZ)  (KMAZ RX),  Russia ’s biggest truckmaker, surged to
the highest price since Feb. 15 after Daimler AG said it planned
to increase its holding in the company in the next three to four
years. The stock jumped as much as 9.5 percent and traded up 7.7
percent at 49.50 rubles.  United Co. Rusal (RUALR)  (RUALR RX), the world’s largest aluminum
producer, dropped 2.5 percent to 219.68 rubles after announcing
a $1.4 billion drop in the book value of its holding in OAO GMK
 Norilsk Nickel . Rusal’s earnings before interest, taxes,
depreciation and amortization fell 46 percent in the fourth
quarter from a year earlier to $382 million, the company said in
a statement today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jack Jordan in Moscow at 
